node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Marco Grassi on July 25, 2021 tagging @flyswiss, @wilderness_culture, @earthpix, @natgeoyourshot, @visitswitzerland, @artofvisuals, @earthfocus, @swiss, @roam, and @bubblehouse_app. May be an image of mountain and nature.

node.text:
Hiking in Switzerland 🇨🇭Exactly one year ago, today, @jessica.lancia and I were hiking in this beautiful area of Switzerland for the first time! We ended up staying two more days than what we originally planned and took it slowly to enjoy the views 💚 Swipe to see more images and a video of our experience. Last slide was made using the evolution module on the @bubblehouse_app and it shows my editing process from start to finish 💫 

Anyone planning to visit Switzerland this summer? 😀

node.text:
Today I want to show you some of my shots as you’ve never seen them before! There are 4 panos and for each one, I’ve added a video of how these same images appear when I upload them on the @bubblehouse_app , using the panorama module. I think it’s just brilliant, and such a great way to showcase my work without worrying about “fitting the ratio”!

By the way, if you haven’t heard of it already, Bubblehouse is an app made for creators. Their goal is to make creators’ life easier, they want us to have complete freedom on the sharing process. They provide 7 different modules with tons of options so that we can have all the control we need to make sure the images are showing and appearing just as we want them to ✨
 If you download Bubblehouse, come say hi, my nickname is “MarcoGrassi” over there 👋🏻

node.text:
Meet the puffins of Mykines, in the Faroe Islands 🇫🇴 These are for sure the cutest and most hilarious birds I have ever seen. If you spend enough time around them, you might as well never want to leave 🐧 The way they fill their beaks with dozens of fish, flying in a clumsy way and land-crashing to reach their holes, always makes me smile 😃

Have you ever seen a puffin?

node.text:
Immense and remote Namibia 🇳🇦 Join me and @hougaard_malan next May as we show you all the best photography spots in the country! 
.
We’ll visit some of Namibia’s photographic hotspots like Sossusvlei, where we include a breathtaking 90-min flight for each participant 🚁  as well as camping in rarely visited parts of the Skeleton Coast. If you haven’t already, subscribe to the priority list (link in bio) to receive a limited time discount offer 🔥
.
All photos: @hougaard_malan 
Tour details: Link in bio

node.text:
Floating above rivers, Iceland 🇮🇸 I’m so happy to finally share with you what @creyety created using one of my images! He spent two days working on it and achieved this animated masterpiece. The more I watch it, the more it makes me feel like I’m still flying over the Highlands with @volcanopilot 😍

After seeing @creyety work I was incredibly fascinated and excited about the idea of him doing his magic on one of my photos. When he reached out, I couldn’t but say yes. Now I’m just stoked about the result! What do you think? 😀

Swipe to see the original image and go give your support to this talented guy!

Photo -@marcograssiphotography
Video - @creyety
